But more specially it is Winter with them at some time more than at others. As in times of affliction, desertion, temptation and persecution. That is the Winter that in theCant. 2. 11. Canticles the Spirit specially speaketh of. And no maruell if ioy and comfort be then oft-times restrained with them; at least if they doe not then so apparently offer themselues to outward view. Who would expect or require leaues or fruit ordinarily in Winter time from a tree? Not but that the godly haue euen at such times also good ground euen for great ioy and much comfort;
howsoeuer they see it not for the present: or but that they haue many of them many times in many such cases,2 Cor. 1. 5. & 7. 4. as much ioy and com • ort as euer:
